<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in Argentina (
                        Cabot
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d90</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">90</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-04-01T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-04-01T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-01T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/4–146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-01T20:00:00-04:00">April 1, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 1—6:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>923. <gloss target="#t_reEmbtel1">ReEmbtel</gloss> 829, Mar. 22.<note n="13" xml:id="d90fn13">Not printed.</note> Reports received from Brazil indicate
                    that profitable clandestine trade hinders <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss>’s concurrence to proposed natural rubber shipments. Problem is
                    increasingly difficult for Embassy since first quarter has passed with no
                    announcement yet given re allocation for either first or second quarter. Believe
                    it imperative that immediate concurrence of <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss> be obtained or that tripartite agreement be officially
                    abandoned to permit thereby action by US in supplying Argentina’s essential
                    natural rubber requirements.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Rio.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
